## Rule Summary

This rule generating code for a PWA Kit application.


## PWA Kit application definition

A PWA Kit application is a eCommerce site headless app connecting to a Salesforce Commerce cloud backend.


## PWA Kit technology stack

A PWA Kit application is a React based application, using the React Router library as well as the PWA Kit runtime (see: https://github.com/SalesforceCommerceCloud/pwa-kit/tree/spike-scom-integration/packages/pwa-kit-runtime).  
On the component side, it is based on ChakraUI (https://github.com/chakra-ui/chakra-ui) and its theming system.
It uses Webpack as its buildsystem.


## Layout of a PWA Kit project

The pages and the the components used by a PWA Kit application are downloaded as an NPM package in `node_modules/@salesforce/retail-react-app/app`. Any file, like a component or page, that needs to be modified should first be copied to the project folder `overrides/app`. Then it can be customized, the build system will pick up the files from `overrides/app` when they exist.

Inside the `app` folder, there are different sub-folders:

- `pages` that contains the different pages. There is one folder per page. For example, `app/pages/home` contains the home page. When a page needs specific components, not to be shared with other pages, then they are added to a `partial` subfolder.  

- `components` that contains the components reusable across page. There is one folder per component. For example, `app/components/login` contains the login component.


Strings are externalized in JSON files located in `/translations`, on file per locale. This folder is ad the root of the project and is the only file that is not in `overrides`. Each string is identified by a unique id which is used in the code. 


## Rule when updating the code

1. Only the pages and components located in `overrides/app` can be modfied. If they do not exist fromn this directory, they should be first copied from the npm module.

2. Any generated UI should follow the ChakraUI theme principle, and use the Chakra component library when the needed component already exist.

3. New pages should be added to `overrides/app/routes.jsx` with the route to reach them.



